NOTE: This is a basic guide and will require tweaks based on your specific requirements.

1. Get your API keys from OpenAI and Twilio. 

2. Set up a Twilio WhatsApp bot following their documentation: https://www.twilio.com/docs/whatsapp/quickstart

3. Create an endpoint in your application. This endpoint will be called whenever a new message is sent to your WhatsApp number.
   
    * In this endpoint, extract the body of the incoming message. This can be done using the POST parameters Twilio sends to your endpoint. 

4. Once you have the message, you can send it to the OpenAI API to generate a response. 

```python
import openai

response = openai.Completion.create(
  engine="text-davinci-003",
  prompt=message,
  max_tokens=150
)

```

5. Extract the text from the response and send it back using Twilio's API:

```python
from twilio.rest import Client

client = Client('YOUR_TWILIO_SID', 'YOUR_TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN')

message = client.messages.create(
    body= response.choices[0].text.strip(),
    from_='whatsapp:+YOUR_TWILIO_WHATSAPP_NUMBER',
    to='whatsapp:+RECIPIENT_NUMBER'
)
```

Remember to replace 'YOUR_OPENAI_API_KEY', 'YOUR_TWILIO_SID', 'YOUR_TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN', 'YOUR_TWILIO_WHATSAPP_NUMBER', and 'RECIPIENT_NUMBER' with your actual details.
